# Scripted Geography

Scripted geographies are groupings of geography (locations, province_definitions, areas etc.) that can include any of the hierarchical components.
They can be scoped to using scripted_geography: data scope link.

borneo_geography = {
	area = {
		north_borneo_area
		south_borneo_area
	}
	province_definition = {
		riau_islands_province
	}
}

Scripted geographies have their own script lists dedicated to them that can be easily and quickly traversed:

scripted_geography:borneo_geography = {
	every_location_in_scripted_geography = {
		# will scope to every location contained within north_borneo_area, south_borneo_area and riau_islands_province
	}
}

scripted_geography:borneo_geography = {
	every_area_in_scripted_geography = {
		# will scope to every area in borneo_geography or contained within any of its regions, subcontinents or continents.
		# In borneo_geography case, it amounts to the following:
		# north_borneo_area
		# south_borneo_area
	}
}


Whether a geographical scope belongs to a scripted geography can be checked by using:
scope:target_location = {
	is_in_scripted_geography = scripted_geography:borneo_geography
}
Can also be used on province_definition, area, region, sub_continent and continent scope.

They can be localized and shown using [ShowScriptedGeographyName( Arg0 )].

Scripted geographies can also use several geography based triggers and script lists:
scripted_geography:borneo_geography = {
	every_present_country = {
		
	}
}

scope:target_country = {
	has_presence_in = scripted_geography:borneo_geography
}

If scripted geography is to be used visibly in game, it should have <key> localized:
 borneo_geography: "Borneo"